(477, 1, '2014-12-11 23:40:48', '2014-12-11 23:40:48', '<p>It is now 12 years since the Government announced the new Gift Aid scheme and for the Paget’s Association it has been a profitable exercise, thanks to our generous members. During this time we have been able to reclaim a total of £24,420 from HM Revenue &amp; Customs.  This amount is sufficient to fund a small research project or broken down annually gives just over £2,000, which for the Association is sufficient to pay for two regional Paget Information Days a year, or pay for the printing of our ‘Facts’ books.  This is money we have received without any additional cost whatsoever to the Association or its members.  This way of giving is a tremendous boost to the charity and we would like to say a big thank you, to all those who have used the opportunity to give in this way.</p>\r\n<p>For those unfamiliar with how the Gift Aid scheme works, it really is very simple.  If you pay UK income tax, by completing a Gift Aid declaration form on behalf of the Paget’s Association, we can claim further money from the Inland Revenue on any donation you make (currently this is 25p for every £1 donated) under the scheme.   Many of our supporters donate regularly, some give one off donations, whilst others pay a £10 annual membership fee, all of which are eligible for Gift Aid if the donor pays UK income tax, which is at least equal to the amount of tax the charity would reclaim from your donation.</p>\r\n<p>The Paget’s Association like many other charities is seeing the impact on the donations it receives, owing to the current financial situation.  Here in the office, we are working really hard to find alternative ways to boost our income in order to give you, our members the level of support you have come to expect from us.   It is not often that we can get something for nothing, but the Gift Aid scheme is just that. Within this newsletter you will find a new style Gift Aid declaration form required by the Inland Revenue, which we would ask you to give serious consideration to completing, so that any donation or membership fee you make to the Association is further enhanced by the Inland Revenue, without any additional cost to yourself.   </p>\r\n<p>By completing the declaration, you are under no obligation to give to the Paget’s Association now, or to give more than you already do.  However, any donation you may choose to make to us now or in the future, no matter how small, will enable us to reclaim the income tax.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.paget.org.uk/getinvolved/giftaid2013.docx"><strong>Download the declaration form</strong></a></p>\r\n<p>If you are not sure if you have already completed a declaration form or you would like further information on the scheme, please contact Sue on 0161 799 4646 or email <a href="mailto:sue@paget.org.uk">sue@paget.org.uk</a></p>\r\n<p>Many thanks once again to all those who already give in this way, it is very much appreciated by the Association.</p>', 'Why Gift Aid?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '360-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-11 23:40:48', '2014-12-11 23:40:48', '', 360, 'http://92.60.114.159/~pagetorg/uncategorized/360-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(478, 1, '2014-12-11 23:41:45', '2014-12-11 23:41:45', '<p>The Paget’s Association accepts secure direct on-line donations and payments through PayPal, you do not need to have a PayPal account to donate using either a credit or debit card.</p>\r\n<p>If you would like the Paget’s Association to reclaim tax on the donations you make until further notice you need to click on the link ‘ Can we claim Gift Aid on your donation?’ at the end of the Paypal payment process.</p>\r\n<p>Please donate by clicking on the button below</p>', 'Online Payments', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '362-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-11 23:41:45', '2014-12-11 23:41:45', '', 362, 'http://92.60.114.159/~pagetorg/uncategorized/362-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
